Merge branch 'Murphy' of https://github.com/za419/GAMR into Ryan
Update the profile page to work with the session system.

Return login button disappearance
Also fix minor mistakes made in header.php when echoing the login box.
Only serve the login pages when the user is not logged in

Remove a debugging statement I forgot to remove
I added a line in registration to confirm that passwords were being hashed, and forgot to remove it. Oops!

Reorder script imports
This simple change is only needed in case common.js uses SHA-3 outside of a function sometime in the future.
For the moment, this therefore does nothing besides maintain the good practice that libraries should be included before our own code.

SHA3 passwords before sending them to the server - Fixes #24 for now, it will be migrated into a new issue with the relevant part of its content
New files corresponds to a new JS package which is used to hash passwords on the client side.
This temporarily undoes @Murfalo's work on hiding the login submit button when the fields are empty - The client will still not allow empty fields to be submitted, and they have been marked as required so the user agent shouldn't allow the user to submit them otherwise.
The reason for this is simple - At least on my system, those changes did not play nice with mine, and it is my policy to prefer security improvements to UI improvements.
That said, it is my intention to either disable or hide that button depending on if submission should be allowed.

Prevent all hover action on disabled elements - Fixes #23
Every selector in every CSS file with a :hover now also has :not([disabled]).
This should cover every case in GAMR. If not, we can fix it later.
For the moment, this should be applied for every case that gets added. A more clever solution should be sought at a later date.
Fix profile information
Fix issues with new session format in profile page

Merge pull request #30 from za419/Ryan

Ryan

Integrate my changes into @Murfalo's code - Fixes #16
Changes made center around the revision to the .sql initialization file and the switch to the use of session IDs for login.
@Murfalo, the db_config.php file shouldn't have its dbname changed to 'users'. Please migrate to the database specified by the .sql file.
The database is not a database of 'users'. It is a database for 'GAMR', and its name reflects that.
Additionally, if the dbname doesn't match the one specified in the initializer, then one will have to be changed manually before any installation proceeds.
The commits I've made radically change the database. @Murfalo, in my opinion, should take the oppurtunity to switch to the new specification.

Merge pull request #29 from za419/Ryan

Ryan

Fix a pair of small bugs that completely broke login
Oops.. I made two small mistakes, and it took me two hours to figure out what went wrong.
Note to self: Be more careful about parentheses and the use of mysqli_prepare().

Add session removal to logout - Fixes #28 fully
With the addition of SQL queries to remove records for sessions which are being logged out of, #28 is now fixed to my satisfaction.
Also, include/header.php and login.php both require_once() db_config.php, to ensure that the necessary variables for database access are loaded.
